{
  "stem": "1860.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 400.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we started early in the morning.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had to get ready to-- to go out of Plaszow to-- let's say to Emalia to work.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When we would come back in-- in the evening, we were marching five in a row, as I mentioned before, with my grandma, my aunt, my mother, and my-- my cousin.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And very often when we would come back from work, we were called to additional work carrying parts of the barracks that they were building there.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There was always construction going on.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So it didn't matter, men or women, when they needed workers, we were carrying the building parts.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And always we-- I-- I made sure that I am with-- with my mother.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "My-- my-- my greatest fear was always to-- of being separated from her.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Came to a point that I don't know whether she was taking care of me or I was taking care of-- of her.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[BACKROUND NOISE] We were extremely close always.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And-- and every time we would come to-- to Plaszow we-- we would find out that there was an action, or somebody was shot, or somebody was hung.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And there were those-- they used to collect us all in the appellplatz for whatever purpose, either to watch the execution or just simply to-- to-- to mistreat us.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[BACKROUND NOISE] And.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, food was rationed.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was so much so of black bread and some soup.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we were fortunate because when we [BACKROUND NOISE] were going out, let's say to Emalia, this Teckla, who lived on the outskirts of Krakow, was able to come and somehow smuggle in a little bit of some additional food.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that was always helpful.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
